Our Workflows

1. Checkout
2. Test
3. Build
4. Use Build Artifact in this Stage

If anyone of stage fails and get error, it will not moving furhter and dont run next stage steps.

This is Default Behaviours of Github Actions.

Sometime you want to ignore that error / fails stage and want to run next stage steps even your previous stage get fails.

You can do it by using "if" filed.

"if" field -- can be use in Jobs and Steps

To Ignore get error/stage fails, use
"continue-on-error" filed on that steps.